rules: Rule1: If the FinTech fund invests in the AI platform, then the AI platform is regulated by the SEC.
Rule2: Either the AI platform faces an outage, or the FinTech fund launches a token, or the FinTech fund acquires a show.
Rule3: Provided that the AI platform uses blockchain, the FinTech fund is profitable.
Rule4: If the AI platform is audited by KPMG, then it uses blockchain.
Rule5: If the AI platform has a partnership with the food delivery company, then, whenever the AI platform is regulated by the SEC, it uses blockchain.
Rule6: If the AI platform has a partnership with the streaming service, then, under the condition that the AI platform is regulated by the SEC, it uses blockchain.
Rule7: Provided that the FinTech fund launches a token, the AI platform has a partnership with the food delivery company.
Rule8: If the FinTech fund acquires a show, then the AI platform has a partnership with the streaming service.
Rule9: If it is not the case that, whenever the AI platform is regulated by the SEC, it is audited by KPMG, then the AI platform is blacklisted by the SEC.
facts: Fact1: The FinTech fund invests in the AI platform.
Fact2: It is not the case that the AI platform faces an outage.
Fact3: The AI platform is not blacklisted by the SEC.
